From 85c0e0a57c7a2278bcc5b3c2f57661302e111c23 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: TBFS Security Review <review@tbfs.local>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 21:51:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 08/10] F-05/F-08/F-12 + F-03 mitigations: one CloudBackup,
 encrypted token, signed full-state backups
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

shared/cloud-backup.js (new, loaded on EVERY page):
- PAT encrypted at rest: AES-GCM-256 under a user passphrase (PBKDF2,
  310k iterations, random salt; HKDF-split into separate encryption and
  HMAC keys). Unlocked once per page session; a small unlock chip
  appears on any page when auto-backup is enabled but locked. Legacy
  btoa() tokens migrate to encrypted storage on first unlock. (F-05)
- Backups are the FULL normalized state in a signed envelope
  {format, version, updatedAt, hmac, state}; restores verify the HMAC
  and route through AppStateManager.importJSON — unsigned legacy
  backups require explicit confirmation. (F-08, F-03 integrity)
- Uploads write latest.json plus an immutable snapshots/<timestamp>
  file (the old daily/ scheme overwrote the same-day restore point);
  a monotonic guard refuses to silently clobber a NEWER remote backup.
- Auto-backup hooks AppStateManager.save with a debounce on every page
  — payments recorded in Active Loans finally back up too, not just
  settings-page saves. (F-12)

settings.html:
- Page-local CloudBackup (btoa 'encryption', lossy payload) and the
  settings-only save hook DELETED; token setup now takes a passphrase
  (with confirm field); session-unlock row added; toggleAutoBackup is
  unlock-aware; restoreData routes through importJSON; clearAllData
  clears the new encrypted-token keys; reminder log escapes client
  names/notes/responses (F-04); logs behind DEBUG (F-17).

Verified: Node WebCrypto smoke test — encrypt/unlock roundtrip, wrong-
passphrase rejection, HMAC tamper detection, legacy migration.
